text.@value:
Cremation of Nyanavipala Mahathera ("Burgher") in 1971 at the 'Island Hermi-
tage Polgasduwa', Dodanduwa, Shri Lanka.  From left to right (first row):
1) Arthur de Silva, + 1988. (He was a generous Sinhalese Dayaka)
2) Toki Saddharatana (Japan), Shin-priest
3) Nyänananda (Sinhalese), lives on SL
4) Sumanapala (Indonesian), + in Holland about 1983
5) Nyanapala (Sinhalese), Samanera, lives in Colombo
6) Kondanño (Sinhalese), lives on SL
7) Nyänasanta (Sinhalese), disrobed (not Nynänasanta/Dietfried
Regula from Austria)
8) Nyanajagath (Indian), lives near Calcutta
9) Nyanaloka (Sinhalese), * 1900 in SL, + 24 Feb. 1976 in SL.
1914 ordained by Nyänatiloka. Nyänaloka was after Nyana-
tiloka's death in 1957 his successor as head of the 'IH'.
10) Merwin Wijesoonya. Then treasurer of the IH. Later dismissed.
This is a reproduction. The original photo is in the archives of the 'Buddhi¬
stische Gesellschaft Hamburg e.V.', Beisserstr. 23, D-22337 Hamburg. Germany.
Reproduction by Hermann Schiewe, Postbrookstr. 5, D-27574 Bremerhaven, Germany
(Jan. 1995).  No. R XIV/1
